-- Reliance to Set Up 5,000 Retail Fuel Outlets in India, Chronicle Reports
-- Malavika Sharma
-- 2010-07-12T04:03:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/reliance-to-set-up-5-000-retail-fuel-outlets-in-india-chronicle-reports.html

          
          
             Reliance Industries Ltd.  plans to
open 5,000 retail fuel outlets in India, the Financial Chronicle
 reported , citing an unidentified company official.  
 Reliance will first open 750 stations that were shut in
2008 because it couldnâ€™t compete with subsidized fuel prices of
state-owned companies, according to the report.  
 Reliance will eventually increase the number of outlets
after diesel prices in India are freed, the newspaper said.  
